IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: FEED MY PEOPLE'S MISSION IS TO SHOW GOD'S LOVE AND COMPASSION TO HIS PEOPLE IN NEED IN 11 LOCAL ZIP CODE AREAS WITHIN SOUTH ST. LOUIS AND NORTHWESTERN JEFFERSON COUNTY, MISSOURI. WE PROVIDE FOOD, CLOTHING, COUNSELING, AND FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE. ALL CLIENTS ARE AT OR BELOW THE FEDERAL POVERTY LEVEL. 37% ARE CHILDREN, 10.5% ARE ELDERLY, MANY ADULTS ARE SINGLE PARENTS, AND 5.5% ARE MINORITIES.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CORPORATE RETURN IS DRAFTED AND PRESENTED TO THE CO-DIRECTORS AND CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER AS WELL AS THE INDEPENDENT AUDITOR FOR REVIEW. THE RETURN IS THEN REVIEWED IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE AUDIT OF THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND ANY ISSUES ARE DISCUSSED AND ADDRESSED IF NECESSARY WITH THE MEMBERS OF THE ABOVE COMMITTEE BEFORE FINALIZATION AND FILING OF THE 990

ALL DOCCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST TO THE ORGANIZATION'S MAIN OFFICE IN ST. LOUIS. CURRENTLY, FORMS 990 FOR THE PRIOR YEARS ARE PUBLISHED ON THE ORGANIZATIONS WEBSITE. THE ORGANIZATION IS IN THE PROCESS OF REDESIGNING THIER WEBPAGE AND MAKING ALL PUBLIC DOCCUMENTS AVAILABLE FROM A SINGLE LOCATION ON THIER WEBSITE.
